summary: Just wanted to pitch this idea for fans of Champions
body:
Just wanted to pitch this idea for fans of Champions

Champions has a huge roster. And only so many of them have solo books right now. That means there is a lot of character buildings that Jim Zub has to do which means a lot of character interactions are like ?. Honestly, we don’t the relationships of a lot of characters in this book. We never really did. And now with this expansion, character dynamics between other characters is going to be lost.

So here is what I propose, some characters who do not have solos at the moment appear books of characters who do. Now as champions fans, we are used this. Our fandoms are connected. But it needs to make sense.

In Miles book, Bombshell and Victor make sense. Bombshell is part of his cast and Victor stays in Spanish Harlem. He can appear. In fact, the three Champions have similarities in that they each are family ties to crime. And they all live in New York. It would make sense for Miles to just run into them.

Riri is in the Midwest but she frequently travels to Harvard. So Nadia, Viv, and Amka should appear semi-frequently in her book. They all have a relationship with science and Nadia loves her robo-niece. Amka lives with Viv and she needs more exposure anyways. Also, Rayshaun and Joaquin because Rayshaun stays in Chicago and there is no reason why Torres can’t stay with him. So that is Five.

Nadia already has a huge cast, but Viv has every reason to be a frequent appearance in her book. Pinpoint can be there because why not and while we are at it, Riri could visit the G.I.R.L. To stay in theme with girls in STEM. Fernanda should appear here as well.

Then we have Kamala. She is the Dora Explorer of Marvel for teen girls anyways. Her books are catered to have several guest appearances because it is the proported leader of Champions. Her books needs to have Sam Alexander if she is going to space. She is the leader of Champions. Her book should be open season for non-solo Champions.

@ubernegro

It kind of hurt to breathe? That wasn’t great.

He took a step back, away from the car. And then a second. Tried to take a deep breath, and he felt a bit lighter. Which didn’t seem bad, at first, but then a gasp went through the crowd and he realized abruptly that he was on the ground.
